The paper deals with covert communication over broadcast channels, which involves information theory and security aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the adversary's ability to detect the communication, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of time-division strategy and optimal throughputs suggest the involvement of network information theory, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions the use of Gaussian memoryless broadcast channels, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the capacity regions of broadcast channels, which falls under cs.SI (Signal Processing).
